law.text:
The purposes of the commission and community corrections programs shall be to:
Provide the judicial system with sentences to be used in lieu of incarceration;
Develop community-based sentencing alternatives to incarceration for certain individuals convicted of a felony;
Monitor and enforce the payment of restitution to victims of crime and the community through financial reimbursement, community service, or both;
Stimulate local involvement in community corrections programs to assure that they are specifically designed to meet the needs of the sentencing court and the community; and
Reduce expenditures of state funds by increasing community-based sentencing, reducing the rate of recidivism, and reducing revocations of probation and parole.
